They both seem to do about 600 damage for around 245 mana. What advantages do each have? When would you use one over the other? <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyamp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yamp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 4:42:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Topic: Lvl 44 - Shock of Swords vs Elemental Maelstrom </span><hr size=1> I dunno, I'll always go with Shock of Swords.. Shock of Swords will do partial damage on a partial resist, Elemental Maelstrom does no damage at all on a partial resist.. Besides that bit, they really aren't all that different.  Maelstrom is a tad more efficient and is Evocation-based, takes longer to cast though. <p>[60 Arch Mage] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753" target="_blank">Master Rascarcapac</a> < Grey Council > <BR>
Xev</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyamp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yamp</A> at: 8/11/02 4:43:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomegasyphon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 6:01:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   comment</span><hr size=1> maelstrom is a dot and only like 10 mana less. its also resisted alot less <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyamp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yamp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 6:37:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> Resisted less? Personally I've had the opposite experience. <p>[60 Arch Mage] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753" target="_blank">Master Rascarcapac</a> < Grey Council > <BR>
Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The UI Guy</span><br>  Posts: 874<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 10:37:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> The true benefit to the dot from what i understand is that it has the potential to interrupt a caster mob every tick of the dot including the initial payload.<br>
<br>
Veldin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uniden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Niden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 6:54:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   That's a myth.</span><hr size=1> I've done several basic tests that indicate there is no knockback on each tick of Elemental Maelstrom or Wrath of the Elements.  The knockback is only present on the initial 250 damage, and it is just as useless as the knockback on the shock series.<br>
<br>
The method I used was to remove all of my resist gear, debuff myself, DoT myself, and then attempt to cast a spell with a long casting time over the duration of the DoT.  My hitpoints went down, and I never even got a channeling check.  This was also consistent throughout several other tests in duels, and a number of additonal tests against lower level NPC spellcasters.<br>
<br>
As for the value of the DoTs... Well, they're pretty much useless in their current form, Elemental Maelstrom moreso than Wrath of the Elements.  Wrath at least does more damage than our best nuke when we get it, but it is completely eclipsed two levels later by Shock of Swords. <p><font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>NIDEN</b><br>Arch Mage of <a href="http://www.unconquered.org/main_page.htm" target="_blank">Unconquered</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 8:16:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Aggro factor</span><hr size=1> One thing more to be considered is that Maelstrom and Wrath generate less aggro than a nuke of comparable power, since they are DOT spells. So if you have some time for the mobs to die, and dont want too much aggro, they may be worth it.<br>
<br>
The only real downside is that they are not affected by our damage bracelet. So, for the normal situations, it is preferable to use Shock of Swords over Maelstrom, since it will usually do more damage.<br>
<br>
Wrath is a good alternative to Char, since the damage is comparable. For fire resistant (but not magic resistant) mobs Wrath is the way to go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The UI Guy</span><br>  Posts: 884<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 10:46:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro factor</span><hr size=1> Ninden unfortunatly I have to disagree with you. I have seen lower level caster mobs get interrupted on the dot when I tested it when it first came out.<br>
<br>
Unless something in the dot was changed or broken it used to have a small chance of interrupting a caster....not like the shock line was very good at this to begin with. Stuns we do not get except in form of Epic and Post 50 fire and Airpets.<br>
<br>
Veldin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 1:13:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro factor</span><hr size=1> If you spec in Conj, Shock of Swords is more manna-efficient. Not to mention the manna saving earring and damage enhancing bracer work with SoS, not with EM.<br>
<br>
EM is less resistable yes, but SoS is partially resistable.<br>
<br>
These aren;t actual statistics, but let me demonstrate my point...<br>
<br>
SoS is resisted 20% of the time<br>
EM is resisted 10% of the time<br>
However, the 20% of the time that SOS is resisted, there's a good chance that it'll only be a partial resist. However, there is no oppertunity for a partial resist with EM.<br>
<br>
EM consistently does 600 dmg when it hits, and that isn't as much as SoS when the bracer effect is added.<br>
<br>
EM does NOT have a pushback effect after the spell hits. This has been debated for a bit and in my experience, there have been no extra pushback effects. If you really want to interrupt casting, your best bet is shock of blades (that ickle lvl 8 spell).<br>
<br>
Also the aggro of EM is not noticably less than SoS, it is just spread out over 30 seconds, so your pet/group has a longer amount of time to build up enough aggro to stop the mob from pouncing on you.<br>
<br>
